data.text:
LINCOLN, Neb.  A look at all the Gazette-area Cornhusker State Games medalists entering Thursdays competition according to on-line information.

McCook

Emma Graff  first in 1-meter diving for age 11-12 novice females.

Jeremy Shaw  first in powerlifting benchpress equipped for Male Masters, 165 pounds; first in powerlifting benchpress equipped, open division, 165 pounds; first powerlifting push pull equipped, Male Master, 165 pounds; first in powerlifting pushpull equipped, Male Open, 165 pounds.

Karragan Shaw  first in powerlifting benchpress, female teen, 123 pounds; first in powerlifting push pull raw, female teen, 123 pounds.

Cambridge

Konner Banzhaf  first in wrestling scholastic, age 20 or above, 158-160 pounds; first in wrestling takedown, age 19 or above, 160-172 pounds, third in wrestling freestyle, age 20 or above, 160-182 pounds.

Culbertson

Duke Williams  second, wrestling, age 7-10, 85 pounds.

Curtis

Robert Wortman  first, track and field, mens discus throw, age 70-74; first, track and field, mens high jump, age 70-74; second, track and field, mens triple jump, age 70-74.

Trenton

Conner Grose  first, wrestling takedown, age 10-12, 128-132 pounds; second, wrestling scholastic, age 11-12, 132-144 pounds; third, wrestling freestyle, age 11-13, 124-133 pounds; third, wrestling advantage, age 11-13, 132-144 pounds.

David Grose  first, wrestling scholastic, age 9-10, 85-92 pounds.

Joel Priest  third, wrestling takedown, age 13-15, 121-128 pounds.

Palisade

Nicholas Heskett  first, track and field, shot put, age 19-29 Male Masters; third, track and field, discus, age 19-29 Male Masters.

Watch for more results next week.
